The uMPI Class
==============

Jonathan Eckstein, June 1997


The class uMPI provides some simple helper functions to make calling
MPI from C++ a little less verbose.  Specifically, they make the
argument for the MPI Communicator group implicit, 
automatically check that the error
codes returned by MPI are zero, and provide an quick global way to
access process rank and other common constants.  The MPI Communicator group,
comm, defaults to MPI_COMM_WORLD

To use, #include "mpiUtil.H"

At present, all functions are inlined.  

I have only defined the functions I need so far, but I suspect I will
add quite a few more.


Members:
-------

static int rank;

The rank of the current process in comm.  Only meaningful
after calling uMPI::init.


static int size;

The number of processes in comm.  Only meaningful after
calling uMPI::init.


static int ioProc;

The rank of a unique processor certified to perform I/O for
comm.  Only meaningful after calling uMPI::init.


static int iDoIO;

Set to (uMPI::rank == uMPI::ioProc).  Only meaningful after calling
uMPI::init.


static int running()

Returns 1 if MPI has been started, otherwise 0.
  

static void init(int* argcP,char*** argvP)

Calls MPI_Init and initializes size, rank, etc. above.


static void done()

Calls MPI_Finalize(). 
  

static void reduce(void* sendbuf,void* recvbuf,int count,
		   MPI_Datatype datatype,MPI_Op op,int root)

Calls MPI_Reduce in comm with the arguments supplied.
Checks the error code returned and aborts if it is not 0.


static void broadcast(void* buffer,int count,MPI_Datatype datatype,int root)

Calls MPI_Bcast in comm with the arguments supplied.
Checks the error code returned and aborts if it is not 0.

